caption.title: Main airports involved in the spread of pH1N1.
caption.p: Main airports involved in the spread of pH1N1, as measured by the number of transitions to new locations. The airports are New York (JFK), Phoenix (PHX), Los Angeles (LAX), Houston (IAH), Mexico City (MEX) and Philadelphia (PHL). The size of the airports in North America was determined by the numbers of passengers in 2013 as given via the OAG database.
